          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "8b.close, closely \n\nclose接近，靠近；dlosely紧紧地，紧密地.\n\nclosely connected,stand close \n87.il,sick \n\ni以做表语，sick定、表均可.a sickboy.\n\n88. good, well \n\ngood形容词，weu 副词，但指身体状况是形容词.He is well again.\n89. quiet, silent, still \n\nquiet安静的，可以发出小的声音；silent不发出声音，但可以动；stiu完\n全不动，完全无声响.He stand there stil.他站在那，一动不动，也不说话.\n90. hard, hardly \n\nhard努力，hardy不work hardI can hardly believe it.\n91.able, capable \n\nable与不定式to do用capa与.Heis capable of doing \n92. almost, nearly \n\n二者均为“几乎，差不多”和否定词造用用almosb.almost nobody.\n93. late, lately \n\nlate迟，晚;lately最近，近来.I haver't seen him lately.\n94.living,alive, live, lively \n\nliving，alive，live均为活着的；living定表均可；alive定、表均可，定语\n后置；live只能做定语；lively意为活泼的。\n\nall the living people= al the people alive.\n95. excited, exciting \n\nexcited 使人兴奋的，exciting 令人兴奋的.\n\nI'm excited. The news is exciting.\n\n96:deep, deeply \n\n",
          "block_bbox": [
